  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Healthy male and female adults between 18 and 60 years of age.

          -  Body weight proportional to height.

          -  Female subjects must be of non-childbearing potential.

          -  QTc less than 450 msec at screening

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Any clinically relevant abnormality identified on the screening history and physical,
             or on laboratory evaluations or the 12-lead surface electrocardiogram at screening or
             pre-dose.

          -  A positive pre-study alcohol/urine drug screen.

          -  Use of nicotine-containing products.

          -  A positive pre-study HIV antibody, Hepatitis B surface antigen (HBsAg) or Hepatitis C
             antibody result.

          -  Recent participation in another study, use of certain medications, consumption certain
             fruits, juices, or red wine
      </textblock>
